Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy has called on foreign citizens to join the country’s fight against the Russian army in a new ‘foreign legion’. This is coming amid the major military operation launched against Ukraine by Russian President Vladimir Putin. A statement seen by The Nation on the President of Ukraine’s website said citizens of any country could come to “fight side by side with the Ukranians against the Russian war criminals”.   VIDEO: Stranded Nigerian students crossing Ukraine-Poland…     BREAKING: Putin puts Russian nuclear deterrent forces on…     Terrorists storm wedding, abduct bride, others in Niger   Read Also: VIDEO: Stranded Nigerian students crossing Ukraine-Poland border On Sunday, the presidential website published a statement outlining the creation of an “International Legion for the Territorial Defence of Ukraine”. It reads; “The President of Ukraine Volodymyr Zelensky is addressing all citizens of the world, friends of Ukraine, peace and democracy “Anyone who wants to join the defence of Ukraine, Europe and the world can come and fight side by side with the Ukranians against the Russian war criminals.”